                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "problems, especially robotics [7]. We describe the design and architecture of MARLIN and discuss how we trained the agent, the hyperparameters used, and the main assumptions and choices we made during its design phase, comparing our work with other RL- based approaches to CC. Furthermore, we discuss the future directions of this research, of which this paper is just the first step. Finally, we present preliminary experimental results obtained in a real networking scenario, where we investigate the current performance of MARLIN and compare it to the Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) in handling a file transfer task."
                                }
                            ]
