                                        1947,
                                        2346,
                                        2541
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Communication networks are a subtle environment for a RL agent. Packets in modern networks are often transmitted a few milliseconds apart, sometimes microseconds. At the same time, running Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) to update the model during training, or even simply computing a new action, can take up a significantly greater amount of time. As a consequence, the environment might have already changed significantly by the time the action is taken, potentially making it obsolete or, even, wrong. This has been identified as one of the main reasons why it is hard to maintain the performance achieved in a simulated environment after moving to a real- world deployment [15]."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
                    ],
                    "index": 11
                },
                {
