                                        1297,
                                        2547,
                                        2346,
                                        2993
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Furthermore, actions do not instantly affect the agent's perception, as the effects of changing the CwND require some time before they have an impact on the network and that impact is propagated back to the source. As new packets are transmitted at a different rate after an action has been taken, they first need to reach their destination, then the receiver needs to generate and transmit a new ACKnowledge (ACK) message for those packets, and finally that ACK needs to arrive back at the source before any information about the impact of"
                                }
